-- World Bank Says Zoellick to Step Down in June
-- B y   S a n d r i n e   R a s t e l l o
-- 2012-02-15T15:25:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/world-bank-president-robert-zoellick-to-step-down-when-term-ends-in-june.html
The  World Bank  said today its
president,  Robert Zoellick , will step down when his term ends on
June 30.  “I’m honored to have led such a world class institution
with so many talented and exceptional people,” Zoellick said in
an e-mailed statement released by the bank in  Washington .
“Together we have focused on supporting  developing countries 
to navigate crises and adjust to global economic shifts.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sandrine Rastello in Washington at 
 srastello@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Costelloe at 
 kcostelloe@bloomberg.net  